<h4>Wireframe</h4>
<p>When working on the wireframes, I wanted to create an experience that felt simple but safe. Fatigue is always something you should keep in mind with UX, and grieving users are especially sensitive to being overwhelmed.</p>
<p>I made it a point to keep each group of questions short, around 4-6 at most per screen. This way, it's easy to go through, and I could organize questions based on common themes. Keeping things simple also meant less scrolling, especially for those using mobile devices.
</p>
<p>I also recommended adding a Preview option at the end. This feature assures users that they can take a break and come back to finish later. Users had enough on their plate.
</p>

