<h3>Deliverables</h3>
<p>The project delivered a comprehensive user flow and wireframes, serving as the blueprint for the web application's development using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript (React).</p>

<p>I created the design deliverables, and I coded alongside my developer team to create the feature. As we coded, I would go back to the design and make changes if we saw something we could improve along the way. </p>

<h3>Results</h3>
<p>Just a week after launching the fundraising tool, we were thrilled to see our first users successfully adding fundraisers to their memorial pages.</p>
<p>Requests to our Customer Support dropped by 40-50%, allowing our team to help with more urgent matters.</p>
<p>After collecting a few weeks of data, I noticed a pattern of users not fully completing the flow. There was a bottleneck at the login/registration touchpoint, where only 28-30% of users getting to the next step.</p>

<p>After verifying that no bugs or technical issues were going on, we recognized that more data was needed to figure out why users were getting stuck. I will be sharing details of that project in a future post.</p>

				
